🚀 How to Run Your App
Step 1 — Start MongoDB (open PowerShell as Administrator)

powershell
net start MongoDB
Step 2 — Start the Backend (open a PowerShell terminal in VS Code)

powershell
cd "C:\Users\hriti\Desktop\Productivity Tracker -- Advanced todo\backend"
npm run server
✅ You should see: Server running on port 5000 and MongoDB Connected

Step 3 — Start the Frontend (open a second PowerShell terminal)

powershell
cd "C:\Users\hriti\Desktop\Productivity Tracker -- Advanced todo\frontend"
npm run dev
✅ You should see: Local: http://localhost:5173/

Step 4 — Open the App in your browser

http://localhost:5173
